## Initial Observations (EDA)

- Cancellations account for ~33% of bookings — a meaningful class imbalance to track.
- Cancelled bookings have significantly higher lead times (~140 days) vs kept bookings (~80 days).
- Guests with more special requests cancel far less often — a strong negative predictor.
- Online bookings have higher cancellation rates than offline/direct bookings.
- Room price does not differ dramatically between groups, but higher-priced rooms cancel slightly more.

